{"label":"For IPad Testing","id":"ipadtest","list":[{"type":"coloring","id":"color","label":"Color the Balloons","lockAfter":10,"onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"type":"toggle","noScale":true,"title":"உயிர் எழுத்து உள்ள பலூன்களை சிவப்பு நிறத்திலும், மெய் எழுத்து உள்ள பலூன்களை மஞ்சள் நிறத்திலும், உயிர்மெய் எழுத்து உள்ள பலூன்களை நீல நிறத்திலும், நிரப்புக.","width":817,"height":450,"name":"colorballons","canvasColor":"white","colors":["#ff4f23","yellow","#02ff00"],"paths":[{"fill":["M 234 138 C 250 136 269 93 269 74 C 276 30 249 20 231 20 C 193 19 177 62 198 105 C 205 120 219 135 234 138|#02ff00","M 207 137 C 220 132 234 99 236 84 C 239 56 215 38 191 47 C 172 53 159 82 181 112 C 188 128 201 138 207 137|#02ff00","M 152 145 C 173 132 174 61 144 40 C 120 22 72 41 80 80 C 87 105 125 150 152 145|#02ff00","M 109 170 C 120 154 107 111 87 88 C 61 56 14 79 13 112 S 38 155 63 166 C 81 172 101 176 109 170|#ff4f23","M 282 141 C 293 146 336 110 346 85 C 359 49 326 14 287 31 C 262 42 251 113 282 141|#ff4f23","M 176 132 C 194 122 192 61 168 49 C 142 38 114 55 121 88 C 125 106 167 137 176 132|yellow"],"noFill":[],"resPos":{"x":330,"y":213}},{"fill":["M 663 152 C 684 155 718 124 734 84 C 741 45 687 24 663 51 C 647 74 634 119 663 152|#02ff00","M 640 139 C 651 141 698 108 694 79 C 691 47 645 40 632 70 C 618 106 635 119 640 139|#ff4f23","M 704 176 C 744 181 788 154 792 145 C 811 123 800 92 782 83 C 757 65 731 84 718 104 C 703 131 701 154 704 176|yellow","M 665 228 C 684 233 727 210 731 197 C 747 168 719 148 703 148 C 686 147 670 167 665 184 C 660 195 657 220 665 228|#02ff00","M 605 185 C 619 182 645 133 634 112 C 622 83 583 90 575 110 C 569 124 577 176 605 185|yellow","M 548 155 C 570 131 555 85 528 57 C 505 37 449 61 466 104 C 474 126 521 162 548 155|#02ff00","M 510 186 C 521 162 483 106 457 102 C 418 91 386 141 418 172 C 438 191 494 199 510 186 |yellow","M 570 138 C 582 120 573 88 567 76 C 551 46 525 54 515 63 C 491 85 508 113 529 124 C 542 133 560 140 570 138|#ff4f23"],"noFill":[],"resPos":{"x":730,"y":213}}],"extraPaths":[],"fontSize":"20px","texts":[{"str":"உ","x":52,"y":121},{"str":"ம","x":96,"y":54},{"str":"க்","x":151,"y":86},{"str":"ர","x":202,"y":83},{"str":"ழ","x":238,"y":36},{"str":"ஒ","x":298,"y":83},{"str":"த்","x":448,"y":145},{"str":"சா","x":470,"y":77},{"str":"எ","x":536,"y":78},{"str":"ய்","x":599,"y":134},{"str":"ஔ","x":643,"y":70},{"str":"யு","x":700,"y":65},{"str":"ழ்","x":744,"y":118},{"str":"நை","x":675,"y":184}],"images":[{"x":0,"y":0,"width":817,"height":450,"src":"img/general/coloring/girl-boy-balloon.png"}]}},{"type":"dragDropImgLabel","id":"drag-vegetables","label":"Drag & Drop: Vegetables","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Drag the names and drop on the images.","path":"stockimg2","imgWidth":110,"imgHeight":110,"text":"carrot|Carrot\nbeetroot|Beetroot\nonion|Onion\ntomato|Tomato\npotato|Potato\ncabbage|Cabbage\ncorn|Corn\ncucumber|Cucumber\ngarlic|Garlic\nginger|Ginger\ncauliflower|Cauliflower\npumpkin|Pumpkin\nalmond|Almond\nbeans|Beans\nbitter-gourd|Bitter Gourd\nbrinjal|Brinjal\ncapsicum|Capsicum\ncashewnut|Cashewnut\nchilli|Chilli\ncoconut|Coconut\nlemon|Lemon\ncorianderleaf|Coriander Leaf\ncurryleaf|Curry Leaf\ndrumstick|Drumstick\nladies-finger|Ladies Finger"}},{"label":"Domestic vs Wild Animals","type":"group","id":"domestic-wild","ref":"classify-imgs-2","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Classify the below animals as domestic and wild. Drag and drop or click and connect.","imageType":"custom","subjectBoxMaxWidth":"100%","boxImgWidth":100,"boxImgHeight":100,"imgWidth":110,"imgHeight":110,"types":[{"name":"Domestic Animals","text":"cat, dog, goat, horse, pig, cow, sheep, buffalo, donkey, camel "},{"name":"Wild Animals","text":"elephant, lion, monkey, rhino, tiger, zebra, giraffe, hippo, bear, cheetah, hyena, antelope"}]}},{"label":"சரியான விடையை தேர்ந்தெடு","type":"matchByDragDrop","id":"match-2","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"சரியான விடையை தேர்ந்தெடு","fontSize":"1.5rem","dashHeight":"2rem","text":"அகர *முதல* எழுத்தெல்லாம் ஆதி\nபகவன் முதற்றே *உலகு*. \n\nவிண்இன்று பொய்ப்பின் *விரிநீர்* வியனுலகத்து\nஉள்நின்று உடற்றும் *பசி*.\n\nகெடுப்பதூஉம் கெட்டார்க்குச் சார்வாய்மற்று *ஆங்கே*\nஎடுப்பதூஉம் எல்லாம் *மழை*.\n\nதம்மின்தம் *மக்கள்* அறிவுடைமை மாநிலத்து\nமன்னுயிர்க்கு எல்லாம் *இனிது*.\n\n*ஈன்ற* பொழுதின் பெரிதுவக்கும் தன்மகனைச்\nசான்றோன் எனக்கேட்ட *தாய்*.\n\nசெயற்கரிய செய்வார் பெரியர் *சிறியர்*\n*செயற்கரிய* செய்கலா தார்."}},{"type":"fillup","id":"fillup","label":"Fill up - is / am / are","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"options":"is, are, am","fontSize":"2rem","dashHeight":"2.8rem","text":"Anil *is* swimming in the pool.\nThe school bell *is* ringing.\nI *am* Anil.\nShips *are* sailing in the sea.\nI *am* not a rabbit.\nBirds *are* flying in the sky.\nWe *are* happy.\nRaju and Anil *are* friends.\nThese children *are* playing in the garden.\nThe tiger *is* feeling hungry.\nI *am* not an idiot.\nThis *is* a lotus flower."}},{"type":"fillup","id":"fillup-2","label":"Fill Up in Passage","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"options":"is, are, am","fontSize":"1.4rem","dashHeight":"2rem","text":"Anbu *was(are, were)* talented in catching fish. He *always(alway, all ways)* went to catch fish with Madhan. They usually used dhoti *as (for)* a net to catch the fish. Anbu also made fishing rods using sticks and thorns *at(with)* home.\nThen, they shared the fish * equally (equal, equaly) * . Unlike their friends, Anbu and Madhan, were always careful while fishing. They never went *deep(long, wide)* into the pond or river. Every Sunday they would go in search of *earthworms (mosquito, frog)* to use them as bait. They enjoyed searching for earthworms. Once the bait was ready they would go fishing.\nOn Sunday, Anbu was not happy. They were able to catch only three fish. The fish were very small to cook so *they(he, she, him)* decided to grow the fish at home. Anbu filled the jar with water and let the three fish *into(to, on)* it. The fish exerted and swam in different directions. Anbu thought the fish was hungry and dropped earthworms into the jar. But to his surprise, the fish did not eat. He saw their eyes and could *feel (fell, felt)* their fear.\nNext morning, he went straight to the fish jar from his bed. He saw *only (one, lonely)* two fish in the jar. He searched for the fish everywhere. Then, he saw one fish on the *floor (shelf, roof)*. Anbu was very sad and his father consoled him. In the evening, his father got a new fish tank. Anbu *changed (changing, change)* the fish to the new tank.\nThe next day, Anbu rushed back from school to the tank. He saw that one more fish was dead and floating on the *top (bottom)*. He started crying. His father said, “These fish live in the river and lake. Nature is their home. It is best to let them be free.” He saw the last fish swimming alone, and he felt bad. He took the fish to the same *pond (school, ground)* and set it free.\nFrom then on, Anbu and Madhan bought a packet of puffed rice and *fed (eat)* the fish. Feeding fish was their new *hobby(work)*."}},{"type":"selectWord","label":"Identify - Adjective of Quantity","id":"select-quantity","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Identify the adjective of quantity in the below sentence.","multiSelect":true,"text":"I ate *some* rice. He showed *much* patience. He has *little* intelligence. We have had *enough* exercise. He has lost *all* his wealth. You have *no* sense. He did not eat *any* rice. Take *great* care of your health. He claimed his *half* share of the booty. There has not been *sufficient* rain this year. The *whole* sum was expended. "}},{"id":"wordsearch","type":"wordsearch","label":"Word Search","authored":true,"onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"தமிழ்நாட்டில் உள்ள முக்கிய ஊர்களை கண்டுபிடிக்கவும் ","size":55,"fontSize":"1rem","words":[{"word":["செ","ன்","னை"],"marker":[2,0,4,0]},{"word":["ம","து","ரை"],"marker":[7,5,7,7]},{"word":["தூ","த்","து","க்","கு","டி"],"marker":[5,4,10,9]},{"word":["த","ரு","ம","பு","ரி"],"marker":[5,3,9,7]},{"word":["தி","ரு","ச்","சி"],"marker":[0,6,3,6]},{"word":["தி","ரு","ப்","பூ","ர்"],"marker":[0,6,0,10]},{"word":["தி","ரு","நெ","ல்","வே","லி"],"marker":[0,6,5,11]},{"word":["வி","ழு","ப்","பு","ர","ம்"],"marker":[6,2,11,2]},{"word":["சே","ல","ம்"],"marker":[11,0,11,2]},{"word":["த","ஞ்","சா","வூ","ர்"],"marker":[0,0,4,4]},{"word":["வே","லூ","ர்"],"marker":[4,2,4,4]},{"word":["கோ","வை"],"marker":[7,9,7,10]},{"word":["ஈ","ரோ","டு"],"marker":[4,7,2,9]},{"word":["க","ட","லூ","ர்"],"marker":[4,1,1,4]}],"table":[["த","ழ","செ","ன்","னை","எ","அ","ப","ஓ","த","ஜ","சே"],["ச","ஞ்","ய","எ","க","ங","ஸ","ல","த","வ","ர","ல"],["ஐ","ட","சா","ட","வே","ஆ","வி","ழு","ப்","பு","ர","ம்"],["ஒ","ஓ","லூ","வூ","லூ","த","ஆ","ஓ","ஈ","த","ஸ","வ"],["வ","ர்","ஷ","ர","ர்","தூ","ரு","க","ம","ஹ","ஊ","த"],["ப","இ","ல","இ","ஸ","எ","த்","ம","ந","ச","உ","ட"],["தி","ரு","ச்","சி","ண","இ","ஜ","து","பு","ஷ","ட","உ"],["ரு","ரு","ட","ல","ஈ","ய","ர","ரை","க்","ரி","இ","ன"],["ப்","ச","நெ","ரோ","எ","அ","ம","ங","ள","கு","ள","ஃ"],["பூ","ள","டு","ல்","ள","ர","ஃ","கோ","ஸ","ந","டி","ஓ"],["ர்","ய","ச","ஊ","வே","ன","ம","வை","ந","ஊ","ழ","ந"],["ற","ன","ட","ல","ஓ","லி","இ","ய","ஒ","ப","ஐ","க"]],"lang":"ta","showWords":true,"isHint":false}},{"id":"animals","type":"crossword","label":"Crossword: உயிரினம் ","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"குறுக்கெழுத்து : உயிரினம் ","size":55,"fontSize":"1.2rem","words":[{"word":"யானை","marker":{"x":0,"y":1},"hint":"காட்டில் வாழும் பெரிய விலங்கு ","direction":"across"},{"word":"பூனை","marker":{"x":1,"y":0},"hint":"எலியின் எதிரி ","direction":"down"},{"word":"ஒட்டகம்","marker":{"x":0,"y":3},"hint":"பாலைவன கப்பல் ","direction":"across"},{"word":"சிங்கம்","marker":{"x":4,"y":0},"hint":"காட்டு ராஜா ","direction":"down"},{"word":"குரங்கு","marker":{"x":2,"y":1},"hint":"மரத்தில் வாழும் விலங்கு ","direction":"across"},{"word":"கரடி","marker":{"x":3,"y":3},"hint":"இரண்டு கால்களால் நடக்கும் விலங்கு ","direction":"down"},{"word":"முதலை","marker":{"x":0,"y":5},"hint":"தரையில் மெதுவாகவும், நீரில் வேகமாகவும் செல்வான் ","direction":"across"},{"word":"தவளை","marker":{"x":1,"y":5},"hint":"_____  தன்வாயால் கெடும் - என்பது பழமொழி ","direction":"down"},{"word":"வரிக்குதிரை","marker":{"x":1,"y":6},"hint":"சாலையை கடக்கும் போது நினைவில் இருக்கும் விலங்கு ","direction":"across"},{"word":"சேவல்","marker":{"x":7,"y":0},"hint":"முருகனின் கொடி ","direction":"down"},{"word":"மயில்","marker":{"x":5,"y":2},"hint":"தேசிய பறவை ","direction":"across"},{"word":"குயில் ","marker":{"x":4,"y":5},"hint":"பாடும் பறவை ","direction":"across"},{"word":"ஈசல்","marker":{"x":6,"y":3},"hint":"ஒரு நாள் மட்டும் வாழும் சிறு உயிரினம் ","direction":"down"}],"table":[["","பூ","","","சி","","","சே"],["யா","னை","கு","ர","ங்","கு","","வ"],["","","","","க","ம","யி","ல்"],["ஒ","ட்","ட","க","ம்","","ஈ",""],["","","","ர","","","ச",""],["மு","த","லை","டி","கு","யி","ல்",""],["","வ","ரி","க்","கு","தி","ரை",""],["","ளை","","","","","",""]],"lang":"ta"}},{"type":"picturePuzzle","id":"picture-puzzle","label":"Picture Puzzle (Maths)","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"type":2,"stmtStyle":{"justifyContent":"space-around","margin":"20px auto","width":500},"arr":["0 + 0 + 0 + 0 + 0 = 25\n0 + 0 + 0 + 0 + 1 = 24\n0 + 0 + 1 + 2 + 2 = 16\n2 + 2 + 3 + 3 + 3 = 11\n0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 = 15\n5, 4, 1, 3, 2","0 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 = 28\n0 + 0 + 0 + 0 + 0 = 20\n0 + 0 + 1 + 2 + 2 = 24\n1 + 2 + 2 + 3 + 3 = 36\n3 + 3 + 3 + 4 + 4 = 38\n4, 6, 5, 10, 4","0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 = 30\n0 + 0 + 1 + 2 + 3 = 36\n0 + 0 + 0 + 1 + 2 = 40\n0 + 0 + 0 + 0 + 1 = 49\n0 + 0 + 0 + 0 + 0 = 50\n10, 9, 1, 6, 4"]}},{"type":"numberInput","id":"word-prob-2","label":"Math Problems (Class 8, pno: 128)","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Answer the following","isSentence":true,"fracFontSize":"1rem","fontSize":"1.2rem","algebra":true,"list":["The cost price of 16 boxes of strawberries is equal to the selling price of 20 boxes of strawberries. Find the gain or loss percentage.\nSolution: \nLet the C.P of one strawberry box be ₹ 𝑥 .\nC.P of 20 strawberry boxes = ?0\nS.P of 20 strawberry boxes \n  = C.P of 16 strawberry boxes = ?1\nHere, S.P #<?2, ＜, ＞> C.P, hence there is a #<?3, profit, loss>.\nLoss = C.P – S.P = ??0 − ??1 = ?4\nLoss % = ~!( loss/CP × 100 ~!) %\n= ~!( ?5/?6 × 100 ~!) %\n = ?7 %\n20𝑥, 16𝑥, ＜, loss, 4𝑥, 4𝑥, 20𝑥, 20"]}},{"type":"balance","label":"Balance the Numbers","id":"balance","data":{"left":"x0,x","right":"?","count":10}}]}